   <body>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>Connect your laptop to the service port (J405) located
on the rear side of the front panel (A810).</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <note>Use the service port cable 940â€“0024D for the
proper connection of all required signals.</note>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Launch the UPS Tuner application and click <uicontrol>Next</uicontrol> in the window that appears.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <note>If the connection fails, you can reconnect, by clicking <uicontrol>Communication</uicontrol> &gt; <uicontrol>Connect</uicontrol> in the
top menu bar.</note>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Select the module you can want to configure: if you want
to configure the HMI, select <uicontrol>Display Module (HMI)</uicontrol>, and if you want to configure the controller box, select <uicontrol>Controller Box</uicontrol>, then click <uicontrol>Next.</uicontrol>
            </p>
            <stepxmp>
               <fig>
                  <image href="../Images/upstuner_selectmodule_0000117112.png"
                         scalefit="yes"
                         translate="no"
                         xml:lang="en"
                         placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Follow the instructions on your laptop.</p>
            <stepxmp>
               <note>If the connection fails, check the communication ports
via the menu <uicontrol>Communications</uicontrol> &gt; <uicontrol>Set
communication parameters</uicontrol> and adjust if needed. All other
parameters are configured automatically to be compatible with the
UPS for both the HMI and the controller box.</note>
            </stepxmp>
         </li>
      </ol>
